article.description: Cameron Johnson and Kevon Harris scored 18 points apiece as Stephen F. Austin defeated Drexel 82-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Johnson, Harris lift Stephen F. Austin past Drexel 82-67
article.linkText: Johnson, Harris lift Stephen F. Austin past Drexel 82-67
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Cameron Johnson and Kevon Harris scored 18 points apiece as Stephen F. Austin defeated Drexel 82-67 on Saturday. John Comeaux added 15 points and Gavin Kensmil had 14 for the Lumberjacks (4-0). Harris also had eight rebounds while Comeaux posted seven assists and six steals. James Butler scored a career-high 23 points and had 10 rebounds for the Dragons (2-3). Stephen F. Austin takes on Rutgers on the road on Wednesday. Drexel plays Bryant at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
